KALSHI.name: Kalshi
KALSHI.tagline: America's first federally regulated prediction market exchange for trading on real-world events
KALSHI.overview: Kalshi is America's first federally regulated prediction market exchange, founded in 2018 by Tarek Mansour and Luana Lopes Lara. The platform allows users to trade event contracts on real-world outcomes, from political elections and economic indicators to sports, weather, and cultural events. After an 18-month regulatory journey, Kalshi received designation as a contract market from the CFTC in November 2020 and launched its trading platform in July 2021. The company made headlines in October 2024 when a federal appeals court ruled in its favor, allowing it to offer political prediction marketsâ€”the first fully regulated election markets in the U.S. As of October 2025, Kalshi has achieved a $5 billion valuation following a $300 million Series D funding round and now operates in over 140 countries. With 2 million users and $50 billion in projected annualized trading volume for 2025, Kalshi is transforming how people hedge risk and capitalize on their knowledge of world events.

investors.name: Event Contracts: Yes/No contracts on future events priced between $0.01-$0.99.

KRAKEN.name: Kraken
KRAKEN.tagline: Global crypto exchange and financial services platform
KRAKEN.overview: Kraken was founded in 2011 and has grown into one of the world's most trusted digital asset platforms. It offers spot and margin trading, futures up to 50x, staking, fiat on-ramps in USD, EUR, GBP, JPY, CAD, AUD, CHF, and institutional services. The exchange serves 15M+ clients across 190+ countries and emphasises security with cold storage, mandatory 2FA, PGP encryption, fraud monitoring and recurring Proof of Reserves audits. In Q1 2025, Kraken generated $472M in revenue and $187M in adjusted EBITDA, marking a 19% year-over-year revenue increase. Tracxn Score: 77.95. Unicorn since 2019.
